texts.text: >In the suburbs of Tokyo—

>Dx2s fight for survival
in a deep darkness.
*Roars, Snarls*
*Groans*
*Screams*
Monsters! Somebody help!

You guys over there!
Hide behind me!
Devil Download!
*Yelps*
*Groans*
Yeah, they're balking now.
Stand up, you two!
We'll hold them off here.

You guys hurry ahead and meet up
with my people. Run!
R-Right!
They've gone.
Hikaru, I've got your back!

Thank you. Now, I can focus on
getting rid of these demons.

>The young man called Hikaru
looks out into the dark.

>Demons emerge,
one after another.

*Cackles* We finally have their
backs against the wall.

Damn you, scurrying around
like mice.

Nice of you to show yourselves,
demons.

The civilians are evacuated.
Now, you're mine.

Start praying. I'm not
holding back.

>The young man readies
his smartphone.
>But then—

*Cackles* "The civilians are
evacuated," he says.
Counting chickens early, huh?
What are you talking about?
*Screams*

>Someone's death throes
reverberate in the distance.
That scream.

Too bad! Aw, I bet you thought
you saved them all.

*Cackles* Foolish. Foolish
human.
Damn it.
You bastards!

>With the battle ended, a heavy
silence falls.

>Hikaru stands amidst the ruins
and the stench of blood.

>At his feet lie the bodies of
several victims.
Hikaru, you fought well.

It's, uh, good we managed
to drive them off.
Hikaru?

>Hikaru silently swats away
an ally's comforting hand.
Hey.
Damn it, not again.
I let people die again.
Hikaru. It's not your fault.
*Groans*
*Howls*
>Liberators' hideout, Tokyo
Megakin, you have a visitor.
Hm? A visitor?

Oh? Was someone scheduled
to come by?
>News spreads quickly.

>The other members pause their
various tasks to assemble.
Please, come in.

Okay. Whoa! The interior design
of this place is crazy!

Well, I guess when your branch
leader is Megakin the MegaTuber.

Totally different from the
Chiba Branch's stuffy office.

*Laughs* Thanks, yo.
I'll take that as a compliment.

She seems very...lively, doesn't
she? Our new guest.
What, like Ririn 2.0?
And you, miss? You know Rika?
Nope. Just met at the entrance.

She said she had something to
discuss, so I invited her in.

She did seem well-informed
about the Liberators.

Seems that way.
Might you be a Dx2 as well?

Who, me? Nah. Who'd wanna be
a Dx2!

Well, uh, we would. All of us
are Dx2.
Oh, right! Sorry!

Didn't mean to be rude.
It's a habit.

But, um, let me introduce
myself. I'm Akari.

My twin brother is a Dx2 at a
different branch.
Your brother? I see.

That would explain why you know
about us.

But what brings ya all the way
out here?
Well, it's actually about him.

My brother, Hikaru. He's gone
missing.
Could you help me look for him?
A Dx2 disappearance, huh?
And you last saw him a week ago.

People at the branch saw him go
out alone for an investigation.
And then he vanished.

Apparently, he was near a place
the Liberators call Aura Gate.
Went missing near the entrance.

But his people and I aren't
familiar with Tokyo Aura Gates.

That's why I came here. To ask
specialists for help.

Aura Gate specialist, you say?
Look no further than Seiran!
You can count on her to help.
Oh, stop it, Jeng Yun!
Well, it is true, I suppose.

But why'd you, a non-Dx2,
come here?

I ain't heard from the other
branch leader.
Yeah, I came out here on my own.

They said they'd call you today.
But I couldn't wait around.

Kind of figured this already,
but you're a headstrong lady.

They just seemed so busy.
It's always like that over there.

When was it? Didn't the
Liberators almost get wiped out?

Hikaru said they couldn't
contact HQ or other branches.

Apparently, even members of the
same branch were spread thin.

Feels like they have their hands
full, even now.
I had no idea.
Then there's the home front!

My parents don't know about Dx2.
They're more worried than I am!

I can't take watching them look
so sad. And I'm free, anyway.
So... Please.
Won't you help me find Hikaru?
Leave it to us.
You even have to ask?
Indeed.

Your brother is missing. I can
imagine your anxiety.
We will aid you.
My, aren't we in a mood, [sys user_name]?
Or are we feeling bashful?

Anyway, as the Liberators, it's
an obvious "yes" from us.

But we're in the middle of
another investigation right now.
So, we gotta split up.
An investigation?

A strange social media challenge
that's gone viral.

Seen it? Talking about so-and-so
is the one true whatever.

Oh, you mean the video where
they're praying, like, way hard?

I remember seeing it and
wondering why it was a thing.

Like, tons of people are sharing
it for funsies, right?

Wouldn't be a problem if it were
just some regular viral video.

But check it, we think it's gone
viral 'cause of demons.

It certainly has the air of some
kind of religious ceremony.

Which is why we got curious and
decided to investigate.

So, we searched. But we've been
unable to find the source.
Huh? Is that even possible?

With our resident hacker on the
case, it normally wouldn't be.

That's why we're thinkin' this
might not be a normal case, yo.

So, we're investigating to see
if demons could be the cause.

Though, we have no idea why
they would do this.

Aight, let's go ahead and decide
the groups.
Out of the folks we have here...

Seiran, Rika, Meat Balloon,
Jeng Yun, and I will head out.
What about me?
What about me?
So, what, I'm hideout-sitting?

[sys user_name],
I want you to help Shiang Sun.

Do you really have to sound
so disappointed?
Good to have you, Newbie.

Now, we can't afford to
dillydally.
Aura Gate is vast.

Hikaru might have gone inside,
so we should find him quickly.
Yes, we should go.

Okay, Liberators!
To Aura Gate!
